70,0.15799536,-0.00545183,0.03053761,0.00421768,-0.05009157,0.04183429,0.00150067,0.02701642,0.01202019,0.00172369,0.06034154,-0.03273636,0.00860693,0.01406774,0.03525060,0.08856968,0.07551554,0.00013929,-0.06466917,-0.02936860,0.03101334,-0.04010098,0.00364042,0.09022760,-0.07642774,-0.08129726,-0.01077981,0.02184822,-0.02248920,0.02674865,0.03577841,0.05704454,-0.00265253,0.00592872,-0.03576611,-0.08140075,0.03344810,0.03914272,0.05180608,-0.08873709,0.11050962,0.03798143,-0.03182346]',E'Service definition\n\n- Bidirectional streaming RPCs where both sides send a sequence of messages\n  using a read-write stream. The two streams operate independently, so clients\n  and servers can read and write in whatever order they like: for example, the\n  server could wait to receive all the client messages before writing its\n  responses, or it could alternately read a message then write a message, or\n  some other combination of reads and writes. The order of messages in each\n  stream is preserved.','{"source": "grpc", "version": "1.65", "language": "proto", "title": "Core Concepts", "section_title": "core-concepts", "url": "https://github.com/grpc/grpc.io/blob/main/content/en/docs/what-is-grpc/core-concepts.md", "topics": "grpc,rpc,core,concepts", "categories": "rpc,networking,proto"}');
