76,-0.02095058,0.04669407,-0.01002512,-0.03268433,0.03596070,0.00348206,-0.01741657,0.00104702,0.00766410,0.01425504,-0.03852156,0.02220511,0.00739799,0.00980561,0.04079515,-0.01260466,-0.00612673,-0.02489634,-0.03244847,0.00885355,-0.00550642,0.01285578,0.07506911,-0.04986182,-0.09282085,-0.00348849,-0.00995895,-0.01662894,0.02147032,0.01751698,0.04549579,0.02958593,0.02376920,-0.05161355,-0.00442751,0.02844908,0.03202862,0.06393038,-0.04793301,0.08847050,0.08274808,-0.01886298]',E'Server streaming RPC\n\nA server-streaming RPC is similar to a unary RPC, except that the server returns\na stream of messages in response to a client''s request. After sending all its\nmessages, the server''s status details (status code and optional status message)\nand optional trailing metadata are sent to the client. This completes processing\non the server side. The client completes once it has all the server''s messages.','{"source": "grpc", "version": "1.65", "language": "proto", "title": "Core Concepts", "section_title": "core-concepts", "url": "https://github.com/grpc/grpc.io/blob/main/content/en/docs/what-is-grpc/core-concepts.md", "topics": "grpc,rpc,core,concepts", "categories": "rpc,networking,proto"}');
