069,0.12138682,-0.06699833,0.02749586,0.00807841,0.00340420,0.00075923,0.07419264,0.04372965,0.03216279,0.01994603,0.05522649,-0.03163385,0.01138931,0.00797964,0.00930469,0.05135199,0.00744379,0.00895361,-0.03078977,-0.06119243,0.02091354,-0.04478829,0.04347350,-0.00122245,-0.07898960,-0.08204802,-0.00726205,-0.03639961,-0.07960644,-0.08017059,0.00755088,0.02211434,-0.00879463,0.08260781,0.05880514,-0.02892132,0.05943160,0.02091762,0.01251817,-0.05189173,0.03374773,0.00133490,-0.02395120]',E'Deadlines/Timeouts {#deadlines}\n\ngRPC allows clients to specify how long they are willing to wait for an RPC to\ncomplete before the RPC is terminated with a `DEADLINE_EXCEEDED` error. On\nthe server side, the server can query to see if a particular RPC has timed out,\nor how much time is left to complete the RPC.\n\nSpecifying a deadline or timeout is language specific: some language APIs work\nin terms of timeouts (durations of time), and some language APIs work in terms\nof a deadline (a fixed point in time) and may or may not have a default deadline.','{"source": "grpc", "version": "1.65", "language": "proto", "title": "Core Concepts", "section_title": "core-concepts", "url": "https://github.com/grpc/grpc.io/blob/main/content/en/docs/what-is-grpc/core-concepts.md", "topics": "grpc,rpc,core,concepts", "categories": "rpc,networking,proto"}');
